    "analysis": "We computed per-(cmdb_id,kpi) global P95 thresholds and scanned the 2022-03-20 14:00–14:30 (UTC+8) window. Metric-level anomaly detection revealed a massive, system-wide shift starting at 14:00 with thousands of (cmdb_id,kpi) pairs exceeding their per-pair P95; many pairs also show intermittent secondary segments later. Minute-level aggregation and minute-to-minute deltas identified the largest positive jumps at 14:00 (+242), 14:07 (+176), and 14:13 (+138). Top contributing components at these jump minutes are adservice, adservice2 and various frontend pods. Traces and logs so far provide little discriminative signal (many trace P95==0, no error logs). To localize root-cause components for the two failures we must inspect, for the most-likely failure minutes, which components (nodes or pods) contributed the most anomalous KPIs and which KPIs per-component show the largest severity (max_value / global_P95). This will let us pick the most downstream faulty component(s) and the likely root reason (resource type) to confirm with traces/logs next.",
